import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='Wildlife_Species', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    effect_damage_counts = data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(effect_damage_counts, labels=effect_damage_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of effect amount of damage caused by bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
